[h1]Function Parameters[/h1]

Functions can take [b]parameters[/b]. 
Function [b]parameters [/b]are the names listed in the function's definition.
[b]
Syntax:[/b] [code format="js"]functionName(param1, param2, param3) {
   // some code
}[/code]
[note]As with variables, parameters should be given [b]names[/b], which are [b]separated by commas[/b] within the parentheses.[/note]

[h1]Using Parameters[/h1]

After defining the parameters, you can use them inside the function.[code format="js" codeId="677"]function sayHello(name) {
   alert("Hi, " + name);
}

sayHello("David");
//Alerts "Hi, David"[/code]
This function takes in one parameter, which is called [b]name[/b]. When calling the function, provide the parameter's value (argument) inside the parentheses. 
[note]Function [b]arguments [/b]are the real values passed to (and received by) the function.[/note]

